:INFO
The Chapter That Almost Lost Me
I picked up Atomic Habits three times before I finished it. The first time I put it \
down on page 60, convinced I had heard everything before. It felt like a productivity \
blog stretched into 300 pages. The second attempt lasted a little longer. The third \
was different. I was at a point where I genuinely needed something to shift, and that \
is when the identity chapter finally landed and I stopped resisting the book.

